title: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
Certified copy
chunks.html_content:
You can get copies of documents if you need to prove who owns or has applied for a UK patent, trade mark or design registration.

There are 2 types of copy – certified and uncertified.

You can also request a replacement of the registration certificate.

This is an official document, also called a Certificate of the Registrar.

You need a certified copy to:

  • register a piece of intellectual property (IP) outside the UK
  • prove legal ownership of intellectual property, such as in a court case

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
Uncertified copy
chunks.html_content: An uncertified copy is a photocopy or digital copy of the details on the register. You can use this for research or personal use.
chunks.plain_content:
Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
Uncertified copy
An uncertified copy is a photocopy or digital copy of the details on the register. You can use this for research or personal use.

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
Replacement certificates
chunks.html_content:
A replacement certificate is a reissue of the registration certificate.

This is not included when you request a certified or uncertified copy.

You need a good reason to get a replacement certificate - for example, you’ve lost the original or did not receive it.
chunks.plain_content:

Replacement certificates

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
chunks.html_content:
Use patents form 23 to apply for either a certified or uncertified copy of a patent.

If you need certified copies of two or more different patents or patent applications, you must send a separate form for each one. You can use the form to ask for multiple copies of the same patent or patent application.

Fill in the form and post it. The address is on the form.

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
How much they cost
chunks.html_content:
Certified copies cost £20 each.

Uncertified copies cost £5.

Uncertified copies by email cost a £5 set fee and £1.20 per page.

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
Uncertified copies
chunks.html_content:
Use form TM31R to get a certified copy of a trade mark.

Certified copies cost £20 each.

Fill in the form and post it. The address is on the form.

Send an email to Intellectual Property Office (IPO) sales including:

  • the trade mark number
  • your telephone number
  • the address you want the photocopy sent to

heading_context: Get copies of patent, trade mark or design documents
Uncertified copies
chunks.html_content:
Use form DF23 to request a certified copy of a design registration or application.

You should use one form for each certified copy you’re requesting.

Certified copies cost £30 each.

Fill in the form and post it. The address is on the form.

Send an email to Intellectual Property Office (IPO) sales including:

  • the design number
  • your telephone number
  • the address you want the photocopy sent to
